    "13 I don't know what corpus of text my computer has analysed in order to come up with that continuation.",
    "It could be continually analysing some vast corpus in real time via the internet but I don't think my internet connection is fast enough to enable that.",
    "I am guessing that the word processor is pre-loaded with the statistical probabilities harvested from some earlier analysis of a vast corpus.",
    "But it turns out that my machine is also doing some real-time analysis on the little corpus being newly built right here and now, maybe just specific to this document: I write some new prose, thus: typlop grubston is a beautiful country, a magnet for tourists who come to climb typlop grubston's impressive mountains.",
    "Some of the highest mountains anywhere are found in typlop grubston."
